<br>
For a while there were not many pallies going on naggy raids when I  level able, now there are many. When we were able to take naggy down, unfortunately no book dropped.. To get on a naggy or vox raid now a days is sometimes impossible... let alone if your lucky to get on one that the book is not already promised to someone. yes when I was needed I still attended the raid even though the book was already spoken for if it dropped.. and to this day I still will..  <br>
<br>
People double dipping to schedule raids IMO is wrong.. unfortunately Yes it does happen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->         But there are honest independents that schedule to get a chance..  When they find a home they will join a guild. I have been in guild that had enough to not need any outsiders, a guild that many were too high to go and I have been in a small guild that has 10 good friends in it.<br>
<br>
If you want to stop independents from the dragon rotation .. why not make the rule.. each guild must have at least 5 independents in attendance and that all items must be randomed no matter the drop.. ( not that I see this happening I am just trying to say let the independents have their shot )<br>
<br>
People try and succeed or they try and fail.... Either way they learn and the rotation moves and they know they tried.. Just like every cleric wants naggy dead so one can get at the ragefire dude,  every pally hopes they get a chance for that stupid rare book to drop..<br>
<br>
again NO removing independents and  YES 48 hours ..<br>
<br>
Yes I like to ramble and yes this is my 2 cents....<br>
